=========================================
Not-so-conventional tool to exploit Discord's unlimited file attachment feature for an endless cloud storage solution.

HIGHLIGHTS
----------
- Async Rust implementation using tokio + reqwest + axum + libunftp.
- Supports HTTP and FTP frontends.
- Metadata backends: redb (embedded) and PostgreSQL.
- HTTP supports partial downloads (Range requests).

REQUIREMENTS
------------
- Discord token(s)
- Optional PostgreSQL instance when using postgres backend

USAGE
-----
- Build: `cargo build --release`
- Run: `./target/release/ddrv --config=config.yaml`
- Migrate old master BoltDB to rewrite redb with main binary:
  `./target/release/ddrv --migrate /path/to/legacy.db --migrate-output /path/to/new.redb`

USAGE DOCKER
------------
- Build image: `docker build -t ddrv:latest .`
- Run: `docker run -p 2525:2525 -p 2526:2526 -v "$PWD/config.yaml:/app/config.yaml" --rm ddrv:latest --config=/app/config.yaml`

BUILD FROM SOURCE
-----------------
- Clone this repository
- `cargo build --release`

CONFIGURATION FILE
------------------
- See `config/config_example.yaml` for a full sample.
- ddrv automatically searches for:
  - `./config.yaml`
  - `$HOME/.config/ddrv/config.yaml`
- Or pass explicit path: `ddrv --config=/path/to/config.yaml`
